title: Despite the Fears, Election Day Mostly Goes as Planned
description: There were the usual glitches, some ginned up into misinformation. But voting was largely free of major incidents of intimidation or disruption.
dc:creator: Alan Feuer
media:credit: Caitlin O'Hara for The New York Times
media:description: Voters wait for polls to open at Worship and Word Church in Peoria, Ariz., on Tuesday.
